{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cbf0d87e-debf-42cb-b133-ba9aaa5196c5","content":"Two things change with xUnit.net v3 on MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changes\n\nThe VSTest `--filter` syntax (`&`, `~`) is replaced by MTP's `--filter` syntax using **`=`** for contains and **`and`** for conjunction:\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest / xunit v2)\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP / xunit v3)\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|--------|-----|\n| `&` | `and` |\n| `\\|` | `or` |\n| `~` (contains) | `~` (still works) |\n| `Property=ExactValue` | `Property=ExactValue` (same) |\n\n### 2. Trait attribute → `[Trait]` still works\n\nYour `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` attribute is supported in xunit.v3, so no code change is needed there.\n\n### Updated CI command\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nThat's the only change needed — replace `&` with ` and `.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e547cb81-c670-469c-8613-73cbe68de277","outputTokens":326,"requestId":"67C1:9A895:2A4C776:2EB403B:69FD37A6"},"id":"195b66c8-66d0-41ff-a4d7-006fac554d5e","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:09:03.111Z","parentId":"dd7d87e8-9a15-45cf-a612-0710b8b9af4f"}
